content: Yes, some of Uranus' moons have interesting features on their surface. For example, Miranda has large, steep cliffs and canyons that indicate significant tectonic activity in the past. Ariel has deep grooves that indicate the presence of a subsurface ocean, and Umbriel has a dark, heavily cratered surface. Titania and Oberon both have large impact basins and distinctive geological features such as canyons, fault scarps, and mountains.
